name: Ocean_DC_IC Functional
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  •Origin - QA3/VRN
  •Gateway - QA1/MIL
  •Destination - QA1/DEN


  NOTE:

  • While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charge/rates)
  • In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (BLRTSH2 screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
  •In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (BLRTSH2 screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa

  Steps:


  1.Process a collect house air shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in local currency (EUR)
  2.Process a collect house air shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD)
  3.Process EHO shipment to INV
  4. Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5.Finish the shipments by printing on BLPRT
  6. Confirm CFDATA is clear at Origin
  7.Attach the housebills to a DC destined to a gateway
  8.Print the MNFST
  9.Make sure CFDATA is clear
  10.In Export Origin find on DC reference in DCCOST screen
  11.Enter an amount in the DC Freight Cost and DC Origin Transfer fields., and then hit F1/Post
  12.Find on DC reference in CFDATA, and make sure it is clear
  13.Find on DC reference in gateway DCLOG
  14.Enter DC Destin Cost, and receiving information, and then hit F1/Add Modify
  15.Find on DC reference in CFDATA, and make sure it is clear
  16.Process a new collect ocean house shipment from gateway to destination. Rate and bill in local currency
  17.In gateway consol, attach the original HBLs and a new collect house air shipment to an ICO destined to final destination
  18.Process upto BLPRT screen
  19.Print MNFST
  20.Process ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  21.Make sure CFDATA is clear
  22.Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement

  Data:
  EHO1 – collect – VRN–DEN (Rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  EHO2 – collect – VRN-DEN (Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD))
  EHO3 – collect – MIL–DEN (Rate and bill in local currency (USD))
  DCO – VRN-MIL
  ICO – MIL-DEN

description:
Create an end-to-end automation script for the Ocean back to back shipment scenario along with Origin Consol corrections and validating accounting transactions.

  Process 1 prepaid and 1 collect shipment

   
  Post MCTRAN at Origin Export
  For Prepaid
  Verify II
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice  and Expect all the contents are correct
  Origin CFIT - AR History by Invoice and Expect all the contents  are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents  are correct
  Verify ES
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice  and Expect all the contents  are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents  are correct
   
  For Collect
  Verify HCII
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice  and Expect all the contents  are correct
  Origin CFIT - AR History by Invoice and Expect all the contents  are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents  are correct
  Verify ES
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice  and Expect all the contents  are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
   
  Post Consol Settlement at Destination CFIT
  For Prepaid
  Verify CSII
  Destination CFIT - AR History By Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Destination EIFA - Review Journal and Expect all contents are correct
  Verify CSRI
  CFIT Origin - Review Vendor Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal and Expect all the contents are correct
   
  For Collect

  CFIT Destination - Review Vendor Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  EIFA Destination - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Verify CSII
  Destination CFIT - AR History By Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Destination EIFA - Review Journal and Expect all contents are correct
  Verify CSRI
  CFIT Origin - Review Vendor Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal and Expect all the contents are correc
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   
  Go back to Export Origin and perform Origin Correction
  For Housebill 1
  Export Origin - ICCOST - user should be changing all editable fields: Airport Transfer, Dest Fee Description and Dest Fee (reduce all editable amount)
  Export Origin - HBCOST - user will be in shipRef1 (housebill 1) and updating onforwarding HdLg Gee and CFS Fee

  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice  and Expect all the contents  are correct

  CFIT Origin - Review Vendor Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal and Expect all the contents are correct

  Destination CFIT - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
